On Fri, 27 Sep 2002, Jason Elm wrote:

> Sachs clutch with 3000 miles on it:
>
> My clutch is making a whirring, light scraping noise
> when I push in the clutch pedal. It gets worse as I
> push the pedal to the ground.


Definitely a throwout bearing.  Replace ASAP.  Make sure the throwout fork
isn't worn thin, and safety-wire the clips into place.

George
